---
import { Image } from "astro:assets";
import MainHead from "../../components/MainHead.astro";
import Nav from "../../components/Nav.astro";
import Footer from "../../components/Footer.astro";

import QBHero from "../portfolio/quotingbill/qb-cancellations-selected.jpg";
import QBWireframe from "../portfolio/quotingbill/qb-wireframe.jpg";
import QBbbSubWCancel from "../portfolio/quotingbill/qb-breadboard-subs-cancellations.jpg";
import QBbbSubWLog from "../portfolio/quotingbill/qb-breadboard-subs-w-log.jpg";
import QBbbSubWBucket from "../portfolio/quotingbill/qb-breadboard-subs-w-bucket.jpg";
import QBFatMBuck from "../portfolio/quotingbill/qb-fatmarker-bucket.jpg";
import QBFatMSel from "../portfolio/quotingbill/qb-fatmarker-selection-to-bucket.jpg";
import QBBucket from "../portfolio/quotingbill/qb-bucket-prototype.jpg";
import QBInvoice from "../portfolio/quotingbill/qb-invoice.png";
import QBProjects from "../portfolio/quotingbill/qb-projects.png";
import QBUsers from "../portfolio/quotingbill/qb-users.png";
import QBProvFrn from "../portfolio/quotingbill/qb-provisioning-frontpage.png";
---

<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <MainHead
      title="QuotingBill — Case Study | Priisma"
      description="How Priisma designed QuotingBill — a recurring billing platform that made telecom invoicing simple, trackable, and built for the people actually running it."
      canonical="https://www.priisma.com/work/quotingbill"
      image="/assets/mesh-gradient.jpg"
    />
  </head>

  <body class="body-base">

    <header class="nav-floater">
      <Nav />
    </header>

    <main>

      <!-- ============================================================
           HERO
      ============================================================ -->
      <section class="section-space min-h-screen bg-linear-(--qb-gradient) text-whiterabbit">
        <div class="mx-auto max-w-7xl">
          <p class="eyebrow">Case Study</p>
          <p class="mt-3 text-xs tracking-widest uppercase opacity-40">Product Design · Front-end Development · UX Research</p>
          <h1 class="mt-8 font-display text-3xl sm:text-4xl lg:text-5xl max-w-4xl leading-[1.05]">
            Making telecom billing feel like it was built for humans.
          </h1>
          <p class="mt-6 max-w-lg text-base opacity-80">
            Deep research, deliberate design, and a platform that shipped.
          </p>
          <div class="mt-16">
            <figure>
              <Image
                src={QBHero}
                sizes="(max-width: 1280px) 100vw, 1280px"
                alt="QuotingBill — customers page showing products selected for cancellation"
                class="w-full border border-current/20"
                loading="eager"
              />
            </figure>
          </div>
          <p class="mt-12 text-center text-xl opacity-30" aria-hidden="true">↓</p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- ============================================================
           CHALLENGE + APPROACH
      ============================================================ -->
      <section class="section-space bg-paper text-ink border-t border-current/10">
        <div class="grid items-start gap-12 mx-auto max-w-7xl md:grid-cols-2">
          <div>
            <p class="eyebrow mb-4">The Challenge</p>
            <p class="text-base">Telecom billing is a mess. Carriers were stuck with slow, overly complex invoicing tools that couldn't keep up with metered usage, cancellations, and provisioning at scale. QuotingBill entered the market with an ambitious goal: make recurring billing feel genuinely simple for the people actually running it — not just the engineers who built it.</p>
          </div>
          <div>
            <p class="eyebrow mb-4">The Approach</p>
            <p class="text-base">Deep market research first — mapping what existing tools got wrong and where the actual pain was. From that foundation, the design process moved methodically: breadboarding the key flows, fat-marker sketching the interactions, and building an HTML/CSS/JS prototype before any pixel-perfect work happened. Each section was designed with the full system in mind, not in isolation.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- ============================================================
           01 — BREADBOARDING THE CANCELLATION FLOW
      ============================================================ -->
      <section class="section-space bg-ink text-paper border-t border-current/10">
        <div class="mx-auto max-w-7xl">
          <p class="eyebrow mb-4">01 — Process</p>
          <h2 class="section-header max-w-2xl">Wired end-to-end before anything was designed.</h2>
          <div class="grid items-start gap-12 mt-10 md:grid-cols-2">
            <p class="text-base">Cancellations are where billing platforms earn or lose trust. One wrong step and the user loses confidence in the whole system. The flow was wired end-to-end from the very first concept — mapping what triggers a cancellation, how the activity log surfaces relevant context, and how multiple products can be cancelled cleanly in a single session. Breadboarding first, high-fidelity after.</p>
            <figure>
              <Image
                src={QBWireframe}
                sizes="(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px"
                alt="QuotingBill user flow wireframe mapping the full cancellation process"
                class="w-full border border-current/20"
                loading="lazy"
              />
              <figcaption class="fig-caption">QuotingBill — User flow diagram</figcaption>
            </figure>
          </div>
          <div class="grid grid-cols-1 gap-4 mt-12 sm:grid-cols-3">
            <figure>
              <Image
                src={QBbbSubWCancel}
                sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px"
                alt="Breadboard — steps for cancelling a subscription"
                class="w-full border border-current/20"
                loading="lazy"
              />
              <figcaption class="fig-caption">Step 1 — Cancellation trigger</figcaption>
            </figure>
            <figure>
              <Image
                src={QBbbSubWLog}
                sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px"
                alt="Breadboard — requests and activity log"
                class="w-full border border-current/20"
                loading="lazy"
              />
              <figcaption class="fig-caption">Step 2 — Activity log surfaces context</figcaption>
            </figure>
            <figure>
              <Image
                src={QBbbSubWBucket}
                sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px"
                alt="Breadboard — handling multiple products and confirmations"
                class="w-full border border-current/20"
                loading="lazy"
              />
              <figcaption class="fig-caption">Step 3 — Multi-product confirmation</figcaption>
            </figure>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- ============================================================
           02 — FAT MARKERS + PROTOTYPE
      ============================================================ -->
      <section class="section-space bg-mist text-ink border-t border-current/10">
        <div class="mx-auto max-w-7xl">
          <p class="eyebrow mb-4">02 — Interaction</p>
          <h2 class="section-header max-w-2xl">Fat markers before pixels.</h2>
          <div class="grid items-start gap-12 mt-10 md:grid-cols-2">
            <p class="text-base">Fat-marker sketches kept the thinking high-level before anyone touched a screen. The bucket concept — where products could be collected and managed in batch — emerged from this phase. Once the interaction felt right on paper, the first prototype was built in HTML/CSS/JS to test timing, feel, and flow before committing to final designs. That prototype became the template for how every subsequent section was approached.</p>
            <div class="grid grid-cols-3 gap-4">
              <figure>
                <Image
                  src={QBFatMBuck}
                  sizes="(max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px"
                  alt="Fat marker sketch — the bucket concept"
                  class="w-full border border-current/20"
                  loading="lazy"
                />
                <figcaption class="fig-caption">The bucket</figcaption>
              </figure>
              <figure>
                <Image
                  src={QBFatMSel}
                  sizes="(max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px"
                  alt="Fat marker sketch — selection to bucket flow"
                  class="w-full border border-current/20"
                  loading="lazy"
                />
                <figcaption class="fig-caption">Selection flow</figcaption>
              </figure>
              <figure>
                <Image
                  src={QBBucket}
                  sizes="(max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px"
                  alt="First HTML/CSS/JS prototype of the bucket interface"
                  class="w-full border border-current/20"
                  loading="lazy"
                />
                <figcaption class="fig-caption">First prototype</figcaption>
              </figure>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- ============================================================
           03 — THE PRODUCT
      ============================================================ -->
      <section class="section-space bg-ink text-paper border-t border-current/10">
        <div class="mx-auto max-w-7xl">
          <p class="eyebrow mb-4">03 — Product</p>
          <h2 class="section-header max-w-2xl">Every section designed as part of the whole.</h2>
          <p class="mt-6 max-w-2xl text-base">The full platform covers invoicing, project management, user provisioning, and third-party service connections. Every section was designed with a consistent information hierarchy — so moving from one area to another never required relearning the interface. The end result: a platform that makes metered billing feel manageable, not overwhelming.</p>
          <div class="grid grid-cols-1 gap-6 mt-12 sm:grid-cols-3">
            <figure>
              <Image
                src={QBInvoice}
                sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px"
                alt="QuotingBill invoice page showing billing details and line items"
                class="w-full border border-current/20"
                loading="lazy"
              />
              <figcaption class="fig-caption">Invoice page</figcaption>
            </figure>
            <figure>
              <Image
                src={QBProjects}
                sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px"
                alt="QuotingBill projects page showing active telecom billing projects"
                class="w-full border border-current/20"
                loading="lazy"
              />
              <figcaption class="fig-caption">Projects page</figcaption>
            </figure>
            <figure>
              <Image
                src={QBUsers}
                sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px"
                alt="QuotingBill user provisioning interface for third-party services"
                class="w-full border border-current/20"
                loading="lazy"
              />
              <figcaption class="fig-caption">User provisioning</figcaption>
            </figure>
          </div>
          <div class="mt-12">
            <figure>
              <Image
                src={QBProvFrn}
                sizes="(max-width: 1280px) 100vw, 1280px"
                alt="QuotingBill provisioning front page — full product interface"
                class="w-full border border-current/20"
                loading="lazy"
              />
              <figcaption class="fig-caption">QuotingBill — Provisioning front page</figcaption>
            </figure>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- ============================================================
           RESULT / CLOSE
      ============================================================ -->
      <section class="section-space bg-paper text-ink border-t border-current/10">
        <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl">
          <h2 class="section-header">Billing software that doesn't fight you.</h2>
          <p class="mt-8 text-base">Billing software has a reputation for being dense and opaque — built for accountants, not operators. QuotingBill set out to do something different: make it feel like something you actually want to use. Two years of work across research, interaction design, and front-end development. The kind of project where the process mattered as much as the output — and where doing it right the first time saved significant time downstream.</p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- ============================================================
           ROLE / CREDITS
      ============================================================ -->
      <section class="section-space bg-mist text-ink border-t border-current/10">
        <div class="mx-auto max-w-7xl">
          <h2 class="section-header mb-12">The work.</h2>
          <div class="grid gap-8 md:grid-cols-3">
            <div>
              <p class="eyebrow mb-4">Design</p>
              <ul class="space-y-1 text-sm list-none">
                <li>Market research</li>
                <li>User flow mapping</li>
                <li>Breadboarding</li>
                <li>Fat-marker sketching</li>
                <li>Interaction design</li>
                <li>Interface design</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
            <div>
              <p class="eyebrow mb-4">Product</p>
              <ul class="space-y-1 text-sm list-none">
                <li>Invoicing</li>
                <li>Project management</li>
                <li>Cancellation flows</li>
                <li>User provisioning</li>
                <li>Third-party integrations</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
            <div>
              <p class="eyebrow mb-4">Development</p>
              <ul class="space-y-1 text-sm list-none">
                <li>HTML / CSS</li>
                <li>Vue.js</li>
                <li>Prototype development</li>
                <li>Front-end implementation</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
          </div>
          <dl class="mt-12 grid gap-4 text-sm md:grid-cols-3">
            <div>
              <dt class="eyebrow">Date</dt>
              <dd class="mt-1">2019–2021</dd>
            </div>
            <div>
              <dt class="eyebrow">Company</dt>
              <dd class="mt-1"><a href="https://quotingbill.com" target="_blank" class="underline underline-offset-4 hover:opacity-70">QuotingBill.com</a></dd>
            </div>
            <div>
              <dt class="eyebrow">Role</dt>
              <dd class="mt-1">Principal designer + Front-end</dd>
            </div>
          </dl>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- ============================================================
           CTA / NEXT
      ============================================================ -->
      <section class="section-space bg-ink text-paper border-t border-current/10">
        <div class="flex flex-col gap-8 mx-auto max-w-7xl sm:flex-row sm:items-center sm:justify-between">
          <div>
            <h2 class="section-header">Building something interesting?</h2>
            <p class="mt-2 text-base opacity-70">Let's talk.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="flex flex-col items-start gap-4 shrink-0 sm:flex-row sm:items-center">
            <a
              href="mailto:fede@priisma.com"
              class="font-medium text-ink bg-yellow rounded-none border-2 border-yellow hover:bg-yellow/90 focus:outline-none focus:ring-2 focus:ring-offset-2 focus:ring-yellow/50 px-6 py-3 inline-block"
            >
              Start a project →
            </a>
            <a
              href="/#work"
              class="inline-block text-sm font-medium underline opacity-60 hover:opacity-100 underline-offset-4 focus:outline-none focus:ring-2 focus:ring-offset-2 focus:ring-woodstock motion-safe:transition-opacity"
            >
              ← Back to work
            </a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

    </main>

    <Footer />

  </body>
</html>
